<h2>Local Entity Authority: A Distinct Discipline</h2>
<p>Local brands face an extra layer. Beyond Knowledge Graph recognition, they need Google Business Profile entity validation. The two systems share signals but operate differently.</p>
<p>Local entity authority signals include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Verified Google Business Profile with complete attributes</li>
<li>Consistent NAP across local directories (Yelp, Bing, Apple Maps, BBB)</li>
<li>Geo-tagged photos and reviews</li>
<li>LocalBusiness schema on the homepage with geoCoordinates</li>
<li>Reviews with author entities where possible</li>
<li>Mentions in local news, chambers of commerce, and industry directories</li>
</ul>
<p>A local brand with strong national entity authority but weak local signals will still struggle to appear in AI Overviews for local-intent queries. The reverse is also true. Both layers compound.</p>
